576
00:59:13,408 --> 00:59:16,429
[SPEAKER_03]: As Lisa said, it's one of the funniest things that she knows about.

577
00:59:17,156 --> 00:59:17,997
[SPEAKER_03]: going on here.

578
00:59:18,397 --> 00:59:25,021
[SPEAKER_03]: Lunch is served at 12 noon or sometimes shortly or sometimes long only thereafter.

579
00:59:25,501 --> 00:59:29,164
[SPEAKER_03]: Call 781-483-3042 to make a reservation.

580
00:59:29,724 --> 00:59:30,785
[SPEAKER_03]: That's going to happen.

581
00:59:31,745 --> 00:59:33,166
[SPEAKER_03]: Elders join us each week.

582
00:59:33,687 --> 00:59:36,849
[SPEAKER_03]: And stay tuned for words and music.

583
00:59:38,850 --> 00:59:44,273
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll take a hiatus because we're going to do Juneteenth as our words and music in June.

584
00:59:46,230 --> 00:59:50,894
[SPEAKER_03]: And then we'll take July and August off for the summer.

585
00:59:51,674 --> 00:59:56,838
[SPEAKER_03]: But in the interim, the Jazz Festival will be coming up in August as well.

586
00:59:57,359 --> 00:59:59,400
[SPEAKER_03]: And that's gonna be a lot of fun.

587
00:59:59,841 --> 01:00:06,246
[SPEAKER_03]: How you can help us, your tax deductible donations help to support the mission of the WMCC.

588
01:00:07,026 --> 01:00:09,428
[SPEAKER_03]: Partner with us in carrying this mission forward.

589
01:00:09,728 --> 01:00:14,412
[SPEAKER_03]: Please consider making a tax deductible donation to this vital community organization.

590
01:00:14,882 --> 01:00:17,884
[SPEAKER_03]: You can make a donation by phone, online, or by check.

591
01:00:18,264 --> 01:00:27,489
[SPEAKER_03]: Please contact Lisa Crossman at 781-483-3042 for more information, or to become a membership.

592
01:00:28,089 --> 01:00:31,531
[SPEAKER_03]: Membership has its privileges.

593
01:00:32,672 --> 01:00:44,538
[SPEAKER_03]: So, part of the joy and privilege I've had in participating in the growth and development of the Medford Jazz Festival with my friend and ally, Jonathan Fagan, is

594
01:00:44,953 --> 01:00:50,695
[SPEAKER_03]: the exposure I've gained to his community of musical friends and peers.

595
01:00:50,755 --> 01:00:58,377
[SPEAKER_03]: That access has enriched me both personally and created some open doors for Fresh Fridays.

596
01:00:59,017 --> 01:01:07,540
[SPEAKER_03]: Through those open doors comes tonight's musical guest, Reese Pike and her band du jour, The Silly Billies.

597
01:01:07,700 --> 01:01:11,961
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm going to let Reese explain what that might be all about.

598
01:01:14,440 --> 01:01:28,766
[SPEAKER_03]: She's a collaborator, she's an outreach girl in the Medford Jazz Festival movement, but she's also a wonderful Berklee-trained musician and a current student member of Danilo Perez's world-renowned Global Jazz Institute.

599
01:01:31,227 --> 01:01:33,488
[SPEAKER_03]: And she'll tell you a little bit more about that.

600
01:01:34,088 --> 01:01:43,112
