754
01:56:58,024 --> 01:56:59,625
[SPEAKER_03]: I really love it.

755
01:56:59,645 --> 01:57:02,826
[SPEAKER_03]: It reminds me of Errol Garner when he used to play the piano.

756
01:57:02,866 --> 01:57:05,286
[SPEAKER_03]: He'd sing to the piano while he was playing.

757
01:57:06,707 --> 01:57:07,707
[SPEAKER_03]: Really, really lovely.

758
01:57:09,420 --> 01:57:15,182
[SPEAKER_03]: So that's a wrap for this new live edition of WMCC's Fresh Fridays.

759
01:57:15,202 --> 01:57:23,945
[SPEAKER_03]: We're so happy to be back here at the center and visiting with you in your living rooms or wherever else you may be watching us.

760
01:57:24,585 --> 01:57:32,007
[SPEAKER_03]: Thank you for allowing us to invade your spaces, showing their faces, and sharing our graces with you.

761
01:57:32,447 --> 01:57:37,129
[SPEAKER_03]: Special thanks to my colleagues Lisa and Melinda for subbing in on the word side.

762
01:57:40,472 --> 01:57:46,356
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, and we're always happy to have new friends, so thank you to the Silly Billies for coming to play for us tonight.

763
01:57:46,376 --> 01:58:02,786
[SPEAKER_03]: Give a high five for my man back there, Kevin Harrington, at the community meeting, helping us be live on local cable and the web, and thank you all for spending another evening with us here at the WMCC.

764
01:58:03,787 --> 01:58:08,070
[SPEAKER_03]: Again, we'll pause in June as we focus our attention on

765
01:58:08,585 --> 01:58:16,087
[SPEAKER_03]: our annual Juneteenth celebration, which will happen on June 19th at seven o'clock right here in this room.

766
01:58:17,407 --> 01:58:20,108
[SPEAKER_03]: You'll be hearing more about that over the next few weeks.

767
01:58:21,468 --> 01:58:31,050
[SPEAKER_03]: Next week, Wednesday the 13th, it's an interesting thing that's gonna happen here at the community center.

768
01:58:31,930 --> 01:58:38,172
[SPEAKER_03]: In the city of Arlington, they're spearheading a campaign

769
01:58:38,736 --> 01:58:46,018
[SPEAKER_03]: to paint a fish mural that's gonna be installed at the Edith Fox Library amongst other places in Arlington.

770
01:58:46,618 --> 01:58:52,159
[SPEAKER_03]: And they've been all over Arlington in different groups getting people to paint fish.

771
01:58:52,659 --> 01:59:00,101
[SPEAKER_03]: They give you the fish, they're actually metal fish with a coating so that they can be painted on.

772
01:59:00,761 --> 01:59:05,562
[SPEAKER_03]: And the groups paint the fish and then the fish will all be installed on this mural.

773
01:59:06,029 --> 01:59:06,609
[SPEAKER_03]: Dish mural.

774
01:59:07,269 --> 01:59:17,413
[SPEAKER_03]: So the kids, primarily, in Lisa's after school program, Lisa and Charmaine and Ketley and so forth, will be here painting fish.

775
01:59:18,174 --> 01:59:23,075
[SPEAKER_03]: Any of you that would like to come paint a fish are welcome to come by.

776
01:59:23,095 --> 01:59:28,998
[SPEAKER_03]: And if you can stand the noise, girls rock your boys, we go wow, wow, wow.

777
01:59:29,158 --> 01:59:33,700
[SPEAKER_03]: You can come and paint a fish with the young people on Wednesday.

778
01:59:35,487 --> 01:59:41,533
[SPEAKER_03]: And that's about it in terms of stuff that we have happening in the immediate future.

779
01:59:42,194 --> 01:59:47,900
[SPEAKER_03]: But before we fade to black, here's one more reminder about what you can do to help us.

780
01:59:47,940 --> 01:59:53,105
[SPEAKER_03]: Your tax-deductible donations help to support the mission of WMCC.

781
01:59:53,525 --> 01:59:56,008
[SPEAKER_03]: So partner with us in carrying the mission forward.

782
01:59:56,408 --> 02:00:01,631
[SPEAKER_03]: Please consider making a tax-deductible donation to this vital community organization.

783
02:00:01,972 --> 02:00:05,374
[SPEAKER_03]: You can make your donation by phone, online, or by check.

784
02:00:05,714 --> 02:00:14,560
[SPEAKER_03]: Please contact Lisa Crossman at 781-483-3042 for more information or to become a member.

785
02:00:15,080 --> 02:00:21,164
[SPEAKER_03]: We are supported in major fashion by the generous members of the West Memphis

786
02:00:25,322 --> 02:00:37,127
[SPEAKER_03]: supported by the Metro Arts Council, a member of the Massachusetts Cultural Council, and again to our generous members and donors, we can't do what we do without you.

787
02:00:38,044 --> 02:00:43,648
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, so y'all ain't got to go home, but you got to get the heck out of here.

788
02:00:43,948 --> 02:00:47,231
[SPEAKER_03]: We've been glad to have you sitting in with us tonight.

789
02:00:47,731 --> 02:00:57,197
[SPEAKER_03]: Thanks once again to the Silly Billies, to Melinda, and to Lisa and Gris back there saying, hey, what's happening?

790
02:00:57,478 --> 02:00:59,959
[SPEAKER_03]: Y'all have a good night and come back again soon.

791
02:01:09,622 --> 02:01:11,724
[SPEAKER_05]: I know it was a millennial view yesterday.

792
02:01:11,784 --> 02:01:12,824
[SPEAKER_05]: It was great.

793
02:01:12,844 --> 02:01:13,465
[SPEAKER_05]: You were late.

794
02:01:43,900 --> 02:01:45,101
the guitar.

